<title>Contemporary Leadership, Minor</title>


<text>
<![CDATA[  

  
]]>
</text>
<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<p><span>The Science &amp; Society Program offers a minor in Contemporary Leadership, open to all undergraduate students regardless of major. The minor provides a broad overview of leadership theory and practice, and engages students in critical thinking, self-reflection, problem solving and multicultural education. Students should contact the minor advisor for course selection and plan approval.</span></p>
<p>Consult advisors often to insure timely enrollment in <span class="sc_courseinline"><span class="code_bubble" data-code-bubble="SAS 192">SAS 192</span></span> and <span class="sc_courseinline"><span class="code_bubble" data-code-bubble="SAS 190X">SAS 190X</span></span> only offered in spring quarter once a year.</p>

<h2>Minor Advisor</h2>
<p>The list of appropriate courses may change over time. To request an advising appointment, consult <a href="mailto:eghack@ucdavis.edu">Elvira Galvan Hack</a> in Science &amp; Society (Plant Pathology). </p>
]]>
</informationtext>
